# 📂 Datasets

---

## 1. VSB Power Line Fault Detection

- **Description:**  
  High-frequency three-phase voltage signals used to detect **partial discharge (PD)** — an early indicator of insulation failure.

- **Download:**  
  https://www.kaggle.com/c/vsb-power-line-fault-detection/data

- **Data Characteristics:**
  - 8,712 signals  
  - 800,000 samples per signal (20 ms window)  
  - Highly imbalanced (~5% faults)  

- **Format:** `.parquet`

- **Use Cases:**
  - Fault precursor detection  
  - Signal classification  
  - Imbalance learning  

- **Citation:**
  - VSB Power Line Fault Detection Dataset, Kaggle Competition (2018)  
  - Misák et al., *IEEE TDEI*, 2017 (background literature)

---

## 2. UCI Electrical Grid Stability

- **Description:**  
  Simulated 4-node grid modeling system stability under control disturbances.

- **Download:**  
  https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/471/electrical+grid+stability+simulated+data

- **Data Characteristics:**
  - 60,000 samples  
  - 12 features + 1 label  

- **Format:** `.csv`

- **Use Cases:**
  - Stability classification  
  - Control response modeling  

- **Citation:**  
  Arzamasov et al., *SmartGridComm*, 2018  

---

## 3. EPFL Campus PMU Dataset

- **Description:**  
  Real-world synchrophasor data collected from a live campus grid in Switzerland.

- **Download:**  
  https://github.com/DESL-EPFL/Point-on-wave-Data-of-EPFL-campus-Distribution-Network

- **Data Characteristics:**
  - 50 Hz system  
  - Multi-day continuous recording  

- **Format:** `.csv`

- **Use Cases:**
  - State estimation  
  - Frequency and ROCOF analysis  

- **Citation:**  
  Pignati et al., *IEEE ISGT*, 2015  

---

## 4. IEEE Oscillation Test Case Library

- **Description:**  
  Benchmark dataset for **oscillation source location**, including:
  - WECC system simulations  
  - Real ISO New England events  

- **Download:**  
  https://ieee-dataport.org/documents/test-cases-library-forcedsustained-power-system-oscillations

- **Data Characteristics:**
  - PMU data: 30 Hz  
  - Real + simulated events  
  - ~540 MB total  

- **Formats:** `.csv`, `.txt`, `.mat`

- **Use Cases:**
  - Oscillation detection  
  - Source localization  

- **Citation:**  
  Wang et al., IEEE DataPort, 2025  

---

## 5. PSML (Multi-Scale PMU Dataset)

- **Description:**  
  Transmission + Distribution co-simulation dataset with labeled disturbances.

- **Download:**  
  https://zenodo.org/record/5130612  

- **Data Characteristics:**
  - Millisecond resolution  
  - 91 measurement channels  
  - Includes renewable + load data  

- **Formats:** `.csv`

- **Use Cases:**
  - ML benchmarking  
  - Event classification  

- **Citation:**  
  Zheng et al., *Nature Scientific Data*, 2022  

---

## 6. HIL Synchrophasor Dataset (IEEE 39-Bus)

- **Description:**  
  Real-time Hardware-in-the-Loop dataset simulating realistic grid + communication behavior.

- **Download:**  
  https://ieee-dataport.org/documents/high-fidelity-synchrophasor-dataset-real-time-hil-testbed-state-estimation-and-event  

- **Data Characteristics:**
  - 26 PMUs  
  - IEEE C37.118 compliant  
  - Includes communication delays  

- **Formats:** `.csv`

- **Use Cases:**
  - Event detection  
  - Cyber-physical analysis  

- **Citation:**  
  Hussain et al., IEEE DataPort, 2025  

---

## 7. ORNL Grid Event Signature Library (GESL)

- **Description:**  
  Large-scale real-world PMU dataset from U.S. utilities.

- **Download:**  
  https://gesl.ornl.gov  

- **Data Characteristics:**
  - 1,694 labeled events  
  - Multi-utility coverage  
  - PMU + Point-on-Wave  

- **Formats:** `.csv`

- **Use Cases:**
  - Event classification  
  - Real-world benchmarking  

- **Citation:**  
  Wilson et al., *IEEE Access*, 2024  

---

## 8. IRTSD — IBR-Rich Transmission Disturbance Dataset

- **Description:**  
  High-fidelity electromagnetic transient dataset for **IBR-dominated grids (~40% renewable penetration)**.

- **Download:**  
  https://ieee-dataport.org/open-access/irtsd-open-source-data-and-toolset-electromagnetic-transient-analysis-disturbances-and  

- **Data Characteristics:**
  - 5,500 events  
  - ~1.4 million signals  
  - Frequency range: 0.5 Hz – 4 kHz  
  - ~29 GB dataset  

- **Formats:** `.csv` + PSCAD models  

- **Use Cases:**
  - IBR disturbance analysis  
  - High-frequency transient modeling  
  - ML for renewable-heavy grids  

- **Citation:**  
  Ross & Mahapatra, IEEE DataPort, 2024  

